############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context('Numeric'); $p = 1950; $t = 40;
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML In a certain wildlife reserve in Africa, there are approximately [`2400`] elephants. Sadly, the population has been decreasing by [`30`] elephants per year. Use a slope-intercept equation and algebra to answer these questions. a. If the trend continues, what would the elephant population be [`15`] years from now?
[_]{$p}{5}
a. If the trend continues, how many years will it be until the elephant population dwindles to [`1200\text{?}`]
[_]{$t}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION The rate of change (slope) is [`-30`] elephants per year. Notice that since we are losing elephants, the slope is a negative number. The starting value is [`2400`] elephants. So the slope-intercept formula is
[``` f(x)=-30x+2400 \text{.}```]
In this equation, [`x`] stands for a number of years into the future, and [`f(x)`] stands for the elephant population that year. To estimate the elephant population [`15`] years later, we substitute [`x`] in the equation with [`15\text{,}`] and we have:
[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} f(\substitute{15})\amp=-30(\substitute{15})+2400\\ \amp=-450+2400\\ \amp=1950 \end{aligned} ```]
So if the trend continues, there would be [`1950`] elephants on this reservation 15 years later.
Next, to find when the elephant population would decrease to [`1200\text{,}`] we substitute [`y`] in the equation with [`1200\text{,}`] and solve for [`x\text{:}`]
[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\subtractright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}-#1}}}}\newcommand{\divideunder}[2]{\frac{#1}{{\highlight{{#2}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} f(x)\amp=-30x+2400\\ \substitute{1200}\amp=-30x+2400\\ 1200\subtractright{2400}\amp=-30x\\ -1200\amp=-30x\\ \divideunder{-1200}{-30}\amp=x\\ 40\amp=x \end{aligned} ```]
So if the trend continues, [`40`] years later, the elephant population would dwindle to [`1200\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();
